289d8258d7b3,Low,Compound,[],"<a name=""l-01""></a> File allows a version of solidity that is susceptible to .selector-related optimizer bug: In solidity versions prior to 0.8.21, there is a legacy code generation [bug](https://soliditylang.org/blog/2023/07/19/missing-side-effects-on-selector-access-bug/) where if foo().selector is called, foo() doesn't actually get evaluated. It is listed as low-severity, because projects usually use the contract name rather than a function call to look up the selector."
